This paper discusses recent breakthroughs in machine language processing and proposes future directions for machine language models to emulate the larger system of acquiring, representing, and communicating about objects and situations in the physical and social world. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
